commit.message:
8353067: Shenandoah: Re-shuffle GC state enum for better encoding

This change reorders the GC state enum bits to make HAS_FORWARDED_BITPOS
and WEAK_ROOTS_BITPOS adjacent. This allows aarch64 to encode the combined
mask (HAS_FORWARDED | WEAK_ROOTS = 3) as an immediate value, avoiding the
double-test in weak reference barriers.

Before: HAS_FORWARDED=0, WEAK_ROOTS=4 (combined value 17, not encodable)
After:  HAS_FORWARDED=0, WEAK_ROOTS=1 (combined value 3, encodable)

This enables more efficient code generation:
  andb(rscratch2, rscratch2, HAS_FORWARDED | WEAK_ROOTS);
  cbz(done);

Instead of:
  tbnz(rscratch2, WEAK_ROOTS_BITPOS, lrb);
  tbz(rscratch2, HAS_FORWARDED_BITPOS, heap_stable);
  bind(lrb);
